data.name: richTextBoxTheory.Text
data.value:
The geographical simulation and optimization system (GeoSOS) is proposed and developed by Prof. Xia Li (mailto:lixia@mail.sysu.edu.cn) from Sun Yat-sen University in China. GeoSOS integrates cellular automata (CA), agent-based models (ABMs), and swarm intelligence models (SIMs) for solving geographical processes simulation and complex spatial optimization problems, such as land use change, urban growth, natural protection areas zoning and facilities sitting.
Website: http://www.geosimulation.cn/
References: http://www.geosimulation.cn/Publications.html

data.name: richTextBoxCredits.Text
data.value:
GeoSOS for ArcGIS is an ArcMap add-in software which can be easily integrated in ArcGIS platform to perform simulation and optimization functions. The theory is proposed by Prof. Xia Li, Dr. Dan Li is responsible for software design and development.
Software design: Dr. Dan Li (mailto:danli@geosos.cn)
Software development: The cellular automate (CA) section: Dr. Dan Li
